#---Status api tests---

### Check status (while logged out)
GET http://localhost:5000/api/status

###
# Separator for requests that should be run in sequence
###

### 1. Login first to get a session cookie
POST http://localhost:5000/api/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "username": "testuser1",
    "password": "password123"
}

### 2. Check status (while logged in)
# REST Client will automatically use the cookie from the previous request
GET http://localhost:5000/api/status

###
# Separator
###

### 1. Logout to clear the cookie
POST http://localhost:5000/api/logout

### 2. Check status again (should be logged out)
GET http://localhost:5000/api/status